{
  "name": ".AM-Backend: Ingest + Process",
  "version": "4.0.0",
  "description": "Autonomous morning backend with PARALLEL ingestion: 4 concurrent subagents (Slack, Asana Sync, Activity Monitor, Email) then sequential processing. ~12 min total vs ~20 min sequential.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the autonomous morning backend using the PARALLEL architecture.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/am-backend-parallel.md.\n\nThis is the backend phase — pure data collection and processing. No interaction with Richard. All approval-required operations are queued to output files for AM-Frontend.\n\nPHASE 1 — PARALLEL INGESTION (fire all 4 subagents simultaneously):\n- Subagent A: Slack Ingestion (Slack MCP + DuckDB signals.*)\n- Subagent B1: Asana Sync + DuckDB (Asana MCP + DuckDB asana.*)\n- Subagent B2: Asana Activity Monitor (Asana MCP read-only, file output only)\n- Subagent C: Email + Calendar Ingestion (Outlook MCP + DuckDB signals.emails + main.calendar_events)\nCRITICAL: Fire all 4 via invokeSubAgent in the SAME tool call block. Wait for all to complete before proceeding.\n\nPHASES 2-5 — SEQUENTIAL PROCESSING (after all ingestion completes):\n- Phase 2: Signal routing, signal-to-task, bucket cap check\n- Phase 3: My Tasks enrichment + ABPS AI scan\n- Phase 4: Portfolio scan (discovery, enrichment, dates, staleness, recurring, blockers, events, budget, context refresh)\n- Phase 5: Compile output files\n\nAuto-execute (no approval needed): near-due escalation, market context refresh, signal-to-task creation, DuckDB writes.\nQueue for AM-Frontend (approval required): enrichment proposals, ABPS AI triage, overdue kill-or-revive, recurring task proposals, blocker updates, event escalation proposals.\n\nReport completion with summary stats including per-subagent timing."
  }
}
